i) Commands to Verify & Troubleshoot Network Configuration and Connectivity
🔹 On Router
show ip interface brief

→ Checks interface status (up/down)

show running-config

→ Verifies configuration

show ip route

→ Displays routing table

ping <destination IP>

→ Tests connectivity

show cdp neighbors

→ Shows directly connected devices

🔹 On PC
ipconfig

→ Displays IP configuration

ping <destination IP>

→ Tests connectivity between hosts

✅ (ii) Route Discovery, Hostname & Address Resolution
🔹 Route Discovery
tracert <destination IP>     (on PC)
traceroute <destination IP> (on Router)

→ Shows path taken by packets (hop-by-hop)

🔹 Address Resolution (ARP)
arp -a        (PC)
show ip arp   (Router)

→ Maps IP address to MAC address

🔹 Hostname Resolution
ping <hostname>

→ Resolves hostname to IP (if configured)

nslookup <domain>

→ Queries DNS server

✅ (iii) Commands to View Active Connections & Ports
🔹 On PC
netstat

→ Shows active network connections

netstat -an

→ Displays all ports and their states

🔹 On Router
show tcp brief

→ Shows active TCP connections

show control-plane host open-ports

→ Displays open ports on router
